Yellow Freight System Inc saidits expects 1987 first quarter profits to be substantiallybelow the 14.2 mln dlrs or 50 cts a share earned in the sameperiod a year ago.    Revenues have been depressed by recent price discounting,added costs from expansion programs, lower shipping volumes andincreased costs associated with severe weather conditionson the East coast, company officials told analysts here.    An industry-wide rate hike of 2.9 pct, set for April one,will cover Yellow Freight's upcoming labor and other costs butwill not make a contribution to operating margins, it said. Reuter&#3;